  "market_context": "Price descended from ~3892.0 to ~3835.25 on 1-minute chart, sweeping a short-term low aggressively, then reversed upward into the prior range during NY session (around 09:50 EST). HTF POIs identified on 1H chart near 3740–3760 and 3780–3790.",
  "key_observation": "An aggressive sweep of a short-term low followed by a strong reversal back into the range created a BPR (Balanced Price Range) or Box Setup zone for long entries.",
  "analysis_steps": [
    "Step 1: Identify a higher time frame point of interest (HTF POI), such as a previous low on the 15-minute or 1-hour chart.",
    "Step 2: Wait for an aggressive move below a short-term low (liquidity sweep) on the 1-minute chart, confirmed by displacement candles.",
    "Step 3: Observe price returning aggressively into the prior range after the sweep, forming a consolidation zone (BPR or box boundaries).",
    "Step 4: Define the box using the lows of the consolidation (e.g., 3841.25 to 3867.25) as entry zones for longs.",
    "Step 5: Target internal highs within the range for 2.6R reward, with stop below the sweep low."
  ],
  "outcome": "Long entry taken at box/BPR zone targeting internal highs for 2.6R; no explicit fill or P&L stated, but setup completed.",
  "lessons": "You can enter before a market structure shift by combining HTF POI with aggressive short-term liquidity sweeps and range re-entry. BPR/Box setups offer precise entries with favorable risk-reward when price returns into range after displacement.",
